<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    §3.3.2.5  SW Component Design
    SW Component Design for the Extended Vehicle Adaptive Application

    Part of the Application Design Description (§3.3.2).
    The full Application Design Description consists of:
      - This file                          (SW Component Design)
      - executable_description.arxml       (Executable + SW Composition + Process Design)
      - sw_interaction_description.arxml   (SW Interaction Description)

    Methodology context:
      Produced by task "Define SW Component Design" (§3.3.1.4).
      Inputs consumed:
        - Service Interface Description:         extended_vehicle_service_interface.arxml
        - Functional Cluster Interface Desc.:    see FC INTERFACE REFERENCES section below
      Outputs consumed by:
        - "Define Executable with enclosed SW Composition" (§3.3.1.1)
          → executable_description.arxml
        - "Define Interaction with Applications" (§3.3.1.2)
          → sw_interaction_description.arxml (VehicleServicePPort connectors)
        - "Define Interaction with Functional Clusters" (§3.3.1.3)
          → sw_interaction_description.arxml (PHM, ara::log, ara::exec, ara::diag)

    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    SCOPE — APPLICATION-LEVEL COMPONENTS ONLY (§TR_AMETH_00010)

    This document covers only APPLICATION-LEVEL adaptive SW components developed
    by the application team against ARA interfaces.

    PLATFORM-LEVEL Functional Clusters (§TR_AMETH_00035) —
    ExecutionManagement, StateManagement, PlatformHealthManagement,
    DiagnosticManager — are NOT modelled here. They are pseudo-implementations
    of the AUTOSAR AP platform FCs that in a production system would be provided
    by the platform vendor as separate deliverables. In this project they are
    hand-coded under src/application/platform/ for educational purposes.

    Composition root is main() in src/main.cpp: all processes are instantiated
    there and registered with ExecutionManagement via Register(). The application
    SW component (ExtendedVehicle) is constructed in main() exactly like the
    platform processes — there is no separate process per POSIX standard, but
    the methodology structure is preserved at the class/lifecycle level.

    Component modelled:
      ExtendedVehicleSwc — the single application-level adaptive SW component.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    DISTINCTION BETWEEN PORT-BASED AND API-BASED FC INTERACTION (§3.3.2.5)
      (a) Port-based: component has an explicit PPort or RPort below.
          These appear in the SW composition at integration time.
      (b) API-based: component calls the FC C++ API directly.
          No port is modelled; interaction documented in
          SW Interaction Description (§3.3.2.7).
-->
<AUTOSAR
    xmlns="http://autosar.org/schema/r4.0"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://autosar.org/schema/r4.0 autosar_00050.xsd">
    <AR-PACKAGES>
        <AR-PACKAGE>
            <SHORT-NAME>SwComponentDesign</SHORT-NAME>
            <ELEMENTS>

                <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                     FUNCTIONAL CLUSTER INTERFACE REFERENCES
                     Each stub documents which specific FC API elements
                     ExtendedVehicle actually uses (§3.3.1.3).
                     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

                <!--
                    PlatformHealthManagementInterface
                    Source: AUTOSAR_AP_SWS_PlatformHealthManagement
                    Interaction mode: PORT-BASED (RPort on the component side).
                    Stub required so that HealthManagementRPort TREF resolves.

                    FC API elements used by ExtendedVehicle:
                      ara::phm::SupervisedEntity
                        Constructor:
                          SupervisedEntity(
                            ara::core::InstanceSpecifier{"ExtendedVehicleSE"},
                            ara::phm::CheckpointCommunicator*)
                        Operations (3 calls per WaitForActivation cycle):
                          ReportCheckpoint(AliveCheckpoint = 0)
                            ↳ before WaitForActivation — alive supervision
                          ReportCheckpoint(DeadlineSourceCheckpoint = 1)
                            ↳ before WaitForActivation — deadline source
                          ReportCheckpoint(DeadlineTargetCheckpoint = 2)
                            ↳ after WaitForActivation  — deadline target
                      ara::core::InstanceSpecifier
                        Used to identify the supervised entity by name.
                        Value: "ExtendedVehicleSE"
                        Bound in health_monitoring_manifest.arxml.
                      Transport: FifoCheckpointCommunicator
                        Named pipe: /tmp/fifo_<rpcPort>
                        Constructed in main(); passed to both ExtendedVehicle
                        and PlatformHealthManagement at construction time.
                -->
                <PORT-INTERFACE>
                    <SHORT-NAME>PlatformHealthManagementInterface</SHORT-NAME>
                </PORT-INTERFACE>

                <!--
                    ara::log — LogAndTrace FC — API-BASED, no port modelled.
                    Source: AUTOSAR_AP_SWS_LogAndTrace

                    FC API elements used by ExtendedVehicle:
                      ara::log::LogStream
                        operator<<(string/int/uint) — appends to internal buffer
                        Flush()                     — clears buffer without output
                      ara::exec::helper::ModelledProcess::Log(LogLevel, LogStream&)
                        Wrapper that routes to the ARA logging framework.
                        Log levels used:
                          cLogLevel   = kInfo  — normal operational messages
                          cErrorLevel = kError — runtime_error catch blocks
                      Logger contexts (set in ModelledProcess base class):
                        appId  = "ExtendedVehicle"
                        ctxId  = "Lifetime" / description "Application lifetime logs"
                -->

                <!--
                    ara::exec — ExecutionManagement FC — API-BASED, no port modelled.
                    Source: AUTOSAR_AP_SWS_ExecutionManagement

                    FC API elements used by ExtendedVehicle:
                      ara::exec::helper::ModelledProcess  (base class)
                        Initialize(map<string,string> args) — starts Main() thread
                        Terminate()                         — sets cancellation token,
                                                             joins thread
                        WaitForActivation() → bool          — blocks until next
                                                             DeterministicClient cycle;
                                                             returns false on shutdown
                      ara::exec::DeterministicClient
                        cCycleDelayMs = 10                  — activation period (ms);
                                                             drives the main loop rate
                      ara::core::InstanceSpecifier
                        Used here for the PHM supervised entity identity (see above).
                -->

                <!--
                    ara::diag — DiagnosticManagement FC — API-BASED, no port modelled.
                    Source: AUTOSAR_AP_SWS_DiagnosticManagement

                    FC API elements used by ExtendedVehicle:
                      ara::diag::Conversation
                        GetCurrentActiveConversations() → vector<Conversation>
                          Called once at termination (shutdown guard).
                          If size == 0: logs "no active diagnostic conversation".
                          If size  > 0: logs "active conversations at termination".
                          Not a sustained interaction — single query, no port.
                -->

                <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                     APPLICATION-LEVEL SW COMPONENT — ExtendedVehicleSwc
                     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

                <!--
                    ExtendedVehicleSwc
                    ──────────────────
                    Category: application-level adaptive SW component (§TR_AMETH_00010).

                    Responsibility:
                      Vehicle telematic gateway. Acquires VIN (Volvo Connected API or
                      demo mode), operates a DoIP server for UDS diagnostic routing,
                      advertises service 5 via SOME/IP SD, handles event-group
                      subscription (SOME/IP pub/sub handshake), and reports alive and
                      deadline checkpoints to PHM every activation cycle.

                    C++ realisation:
                      Class:      application::ExtendedVehicle
                      Files:      src/application/extended_vehicle.h / .cpp
                      Base class: ara::exec::helper::ModelledProcess
                        Provides WaitForActivation(), Initialize(), Terminate(),
                        Log() — all API-based, no ports.
                      Constructed and registered in: src/main.cpp

                    Ports (2):

                      VehicleServicePPort  — application-level PPort
                        Provides ExtendedVehicleInterface (service 5) to
                        other applications / platform components on the network.

                        C++ realisation (three parallel mechanisms on one port):

                          mNetworkLayer   — SdNetworkLayer (UDP multicast socket)
                            Shared transport for SD and pub/sub SD messages.
                            Binds to 239.0.0.1:5555 (from manifest EVENT-MULTICAST-UDP-PORT
                            and IPV-4-MULTICAST-IP-ADDRESS).

                          mSdServer       — SomeIpSdServer (IMPLEMENTED)
                            Sends OfferService SD messages periodically.
                            Endpoint advertised: 127.0.0.1:8081 (Machine A)
                                              or 127.0.0.1:8082 (Machine B)
                            Configured via: configureSdServer(reader)

                          mPubSubServer   — SomeIpPubSubServer (IMPLEMENTED)
                            Handles SubscribeEventGroup SD messages from clients.
                            Replies with SubscribeEventGroupAck carrying the
                            multicast endpoint 239.0.0.1:5555.
                            EventGroup ID: 1 (from manifest EVENT-GROUP-ID).
                            Configured via: configurePubSubServer(reader)
                            Note: subscription handshake is complete; multicast
                            event payload delivery (VehicleStatus data) is a
                            planned future step requiring a Publish() API.

                          mDoipServer     — DoipServer (IMPLEMENTED)
                            Accepts UDS-over-DoIP connections on the TCP unicast
                            endpoint (ServerUnicastTcp, port 8081/8082).
                            Serves VIN and vehicle resource queries.

                        Integration binding: extended_vehicle_manifest.arxml
                          PROVIDED-SOMEIP-SERVICE-INSTANCE, service ID 5
                          SERVICE-INSTANCE-ID: 0 (Machine A) / 1 (Machine B)
                          EventGroup multicast: 239.0.0.1:5555 (EventGroup ID 1)
                          DoIP TCP endpoint: 127.0.0.1:8081 / 8082

                      HealthManagementRPort — platform-level RPort
                        Requires PlatformHealthManagementInterface.
                        See FC Interface Reference above for full API detail.
                        Integration binding: health_monitoring_manifest.arxml
                          SupervisedEntity: "ExtendedVehicleSE"
                          EXPECTED-ALIVE-INDICATIONS: 10 per 100 ms reference cycle
                          MIN-MARGIN / MAX-MARGIN: ±5

                    API-based FC interactions (no port modelled):
                      ara::log  — LogStream, Log(level, stream) via base class
                      ara::exec — WaitForActivation, Initialize/Terminate, cCycleDelayMs
                      ara::diag — Conversation::GetCurrentActiveConversations() at shutdown
                -->
                <ADAPTIVE-APPLICATION-SW-COMPONENT-TYPE>
                    <SHORT-NAME>ExtendedVehicleSwc</SHORT-NAME>

                    <PORTS>

                        <P-PORT-PROTOTYPE>
                            <SHORT-NAME>VehicleServicePPort</SHORT-NAME>
                            <PROVIDED-INTERFACE-TREF DEST="SERVICE-INTERFACE">
                                ExtendedVehicleInterface
                            </PROVIDED-INTERFACE-TREF>
                        </P-PORT-PROTOTYPE>

                        <R-PORT-PROTOTYPE>
                            <SHORT-NAME>HealthManagementRPort</SHORT-NAME>
                            <REQUIRED-INTERFACE-TREF DEST="PORT-INTERFACE">
                                PlatformHealthManagementInterface
                            </REQUIRED-INTERFACE-TREF>
                        </R-PORT-PROTOTYPE>

                    </PORTS>

                </ADAPTIVE-APPLICATION-SW-COMPONENT-TYPE>

                <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                     APPLICATION-LEVEL SW COMPONENT — WatchdogSwc
                     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

                <!--
                    WatchdogSwc
                    ───────────
                    Category: application-level adaptive SW component (§TR_AMETH_00010).

                    Responsibility:
                      Cross-machine heartbeat monitor. Subscribes to the
                      TelematicControlModuleEvent published by the ExtendedVehicle
                      on the REMOTE machine (Instance ID 1 on Machine A, Instance ID 0
                      on Machine B). If no event is received within a configurable
                      timeout window (heartbeat interval × tolerance factor), it logs
                      a connectivity warning. Optionally reports via ara::diag to
                      make the DTC U0198 trigger event-receipt-based rather than
                      SD-state-based (see sw_interaction_description.arxml §4 note).

                    C++ realisation (planned — not yet implemented):
                      Class:      application::WatchdogApplication
                      Files:      src/application/watchdog_application.h / .cpp
                      Base class: ara::exec::helper::ModelledProcess
                        Provides WaitForActivation(), Initialize(), Terminate(), Log()
                      Constructed and registered in: src/main.cpp

                    Service interface consumed:
                      ExtendedVehicleInterface (service ID 5)
                      Same interface defined in extended_vehicle_service_interface.arxml.
                      No new service interface description is required.
                      TelematicControlModuleEvent (EventGroup ID 1) doubles as
                      the heartbeat signal — its periodic receipt confirms Machine B
                      (or A) is alive and connected.

                    Ports (1):

                      VehicleServiceRPort — application-level RPort
                        Requires ExtendedVehicleInterface (service 5) from the
                        REMOTE machine only.
                          Machine A WatchdogApp: subscribes to Instance ID 1 (Machine B)
                          Machine B WatchdogApp: subscribes to Instance ID 0 (Machine A)
                        This fixes the Instance ID ANY gap documented in
                        sw_interaction_description.arxml §1a: WatchdogApp always
                        targets the remote instance explicitly, so it will not
                        accidentally discover its own machine's service.

                        C++ realisation (planned):
                          mSdClient       — SomeIpSdClient
                            Sends FindService for service 5 / remote instance.
                            Receives OfferService Ack from remote ExtendedVehicle.
                          mPubSubClient   — SomeIpPubSubClient
                            Sends SubscribeEventGroup (service 5, EventGroup 1).
                            Receives SubscribeEventGroupAck via
                            TryGetProcessedSubscription().
                          Heartbeat receiver — SOMEIP event data listener (PLANNED)
                            Listens on 239.0.0.1:5555 for SOME/IP NOTIFICATION
                            frames (MessageType=0x02, MethodID=0x8001).
                            Not yet implemented — requires SomeIpPubSubServer::Publish()
                            on the provider side and a SOME/IP event frame decoder
                            on this side. See implementation gap note below.

                        Integration binding: watchdog_manifest.arxml
                          REQUIRED-SOMEIP-SERVICE-INSTANCE, service ID 5
                          SERVICE-INSTANCE-ID: 1 (Machine A manifest)
                                            or 0 (Machine B manifest)
                          REQUIRED-EVENT-GROUPS: EventGroup ID 1

                    API-based FC interactions (no port modelled):
                      ara::log  — LogStream, Log(level, stream) via base class
                      ara::exec — WaitForActivation, Initialize/Terminate, cCycleDelayMs

                    Implementation gap note:
                      The subscription handshake (FindService → Subscribe → Ack)
                      is fully supported by SomeIpSdClient + SomeIpPubSubClient.
                      Actual heartbeat data delivery requires two additions:
                        Provider side: SomeIpPubSubServer::Publish(VehicleStatusType)
                          — sends a SOME/IP NOTIFICATION frame to 239.0.0.1:5555
                          — method ID 0x8001, service ID 5
                          — currently no Publish() API exists on SomeIpPubSubServer
                        Consumer side: SOME/IP event frame receiver
                          — must decode non-SD SOME/IP frames from 239.0.0.1:5555
                          — separate from SdNetworkLayer (which handles SD messages)
                          — timeout detection against WaitForActivation cycle count
                      These are the two implementation tasks gating the first
                      end-to-end heartbeat.
                -->
                <ADAPTIVE-APPLICATION-SW-COMPONENT-TYPE>
                    <SHORT-NAME>WatchdogSwc</SHORT-NAME>

                    <PORTS>

                        <R-PORT-PROTOTYPE>
                            <SHORT-NAME>VehicleServiceRPort</SHORT-NAME>
                            <REQUIRED-INTERFACE-TREF DEST="SERVICE-INTERFACE">
                                ExtendedVehicleInterface
                            </REQUIRED-INTERFACE-TREF>
                        </R-PORT-PROTOTYPE>

                    </PORTS>

                </ADAPTIVE-APPLICATION-SW-COMPONENT-TYPE>

                <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                     NEXT STEPS IN THE METHODOLOGY FLOW
                     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

                     §3.3.1.1  Define Executable with enclosed SW Composition
                       → executable_description.arxml
                       ExtendedVehicleSwc is instantiated as a single prototype
                       (ExtendedVehicleInstance) inside AdaptiveAutosarComposition.
                       Platform-level processes (EM, SM, PHM, DM) are co-hosted in
                       the same POSIX binary but are not part of the SW composition.

                     §3.3.1.2  Define Interaction with Applications
                       VehicleServicePPort ↔ DiagnosticManager (platform-level consumer):
                         SD: OfferService / FindService over 239.0.0.1:5555
                         PubSub: SubscribeEventGroup / Ack over 239.0.0.1:5555
                         DoIP: UDS queries over TCP 127.0.0.1:8081 / 8082
                       Cross-machine binding in Service Instance Manifests.

                     §3.3.1.3  Define Interaction with Functional Clusters
                       HealthManagementRPort → health_monitoring_manifest.arxml
                       API-based interactions → sw_interaction_description.arxml

                     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

            </ELEMENTS>
        </AR-PACKAGE>
    </AR-PACKAGES>
</AUTOSAR>
